  "time_ut": 1658226368,
  "original_lang": "si",
  "original_title": "\u0da1\u0db1\u0dca\u0daf\u0dba \u0dc6\u0ddc\u0da7\u0ddd \u0d9a\u0dc5\u0ddc\u0dad\u0dca \u0dc0\u0dd0\u0da9 \u0dc0\u0dbb\u0daf\u0dd3",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "If you take a photo of the vote, it is illegal",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Speaker Mahinda Yapa Abeywardena said today (19) at the meeting of the Committee on Parliamentary Affairs that he would request all MPs to refrain from photographing their votes during the election to select the next president.",
        "In the meantime, it is said from the parliamentary sources that if the members of parliament take a photo of their vote during the polling of the president, they will be deprived of their seat in parliament for 7 years or be sentenced to six months imprisonment or legal provisions.",
        "The speaker said that the support of all the parties is expected to successfully complete the polling to be held tomorrow (20) to select the successor president by adhering to all the rules and respecting democracy.",
        "The speaker also said that he appreciates the support given by all parties so far to successfully conduct the process of selecting the successor president within the relevant legal framework.",
        "Mr. Dhammika Dasanayake, the Secretary General of the Parliament, who is the Electoral Officer of today's secret poll, has stated that all the necessary guidelines have been given to the MPs in accordance with the Election of the President (Special Provisions) Act No. 2 of 1981.",
        "Meanwhile, it was decided tomorrow (20th) in the Committee on Parliamentary Affairs that the Parliament will meet again on the 27th.",
        "The emergency declaration announced by the Acting President under the Public Security Act is scheduled to be submitted for approval on that day."
      ],
